Go to https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/#red-hat-centos (Note: only for Linux)
For windows : https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/windows/

#first dhi jenkins repo ni download cheyyadaniki..
#second dhi vachi jenkins key kosam..connect avvadaniki
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
    https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
dnf install java-17-amazon-corretto -y
dnf install jenkins -y
systemctl status jenkins
systemctl start jenkins
dnf install git -y


Steps:
* Install JAVA on the LX machine.(supported version: java-17-amazon-corretto)
* Then Install Jenkins on it.
* Verify istallation
* Check status of Jenkin services
* Start if not started .
* Then connect to Jenkins Dasboard with publicip:8080.
* It propmts for Password. Get it from /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
* Install necessary Plugins.
Then our setup will be ready.


